        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Protect Drinking Water from PFAS Act of 2019</b></p> <p>This bill requires the Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) to address the level of perfluoroalkyl and polyfluoroalkyl substances (PFAS) in drinking water. Specifically, the EPA must publish a maximum contaminant level goal and promulgate a national primary drinking water regulation for total PFAS. PFAS are man-made chemicals that may lead to adverse human health effects.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
